<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2156] TServerSocket::listen() is throwing exceptions with misleading information</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2156</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to a problem with bind() an exception was thrown.&lt;br/&gt;
The text was:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Could not bind: Transport endpoint is not connected&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
which doesn&apos;t make sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It turned out that errno had been overwritten.&lt;br/&gt;
The correct text would have been:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Could not bind: Address already in use&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
