&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;may be even better. Same with errbuf below, where the literal 1024 is involved multiple times. If someone changes one of these and forgets about the other, we get a nice buffer overflow.&lt;/p&gt;

